1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
Mirai dake shinjiteru dareka ga warattemo kamawanai
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
Hashitteru jounetsu ga anata wo KIRA mekaseru
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
Mabushi sugi, demo mitsumete itai
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
Dokka "bigaku" kanjiteru
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:56.120 --> 00:00:58.160
I'm really really stuck on you

12
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
Dare ni mo nitenai yume no senaka wo
I follow, follow in the footsteps

13
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
Oikakete oikaketeku
of a dream that resembles no one

14
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
DORAMATIKKU te ni ireru made
Until I dramatically get it

15
00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:15.080
Believe in Wonderland!

16
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
Dare ni mo mienai yume no KATACHI wo
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

17
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
Tsukamaete tsukamaeteku
of a dream no one can see

18
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
Watashi wa tsuite yuku kara atsui KIMOCHI
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

19
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
TSUJITSUMA awase betsu ni iranai
I don't really need everything to add up

20
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Arifureta nichijou yori mo
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

21
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
PARADAISU mezashite hashire
run for paradise instead

22
00:01:40.390 --> 00:01:45.920
Believe in Wonderland!

23
00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:55.600
Tsunami!

24
00:01:55.600 --> 00:01:56.800
What now?

25
00:01:56.800 --> 00:01:58.470
A tsunami's coming!

26
00:01:58.470 --> 00:02:00.100
What's going on, Luffy?!

27
00:02:00.100 --> 00:02:02.730
Maybe it wasn't
such a good idea after all?

28
00:02:02.730 --> 00:02:04.190
What wasn't a good idea?

29
00:02:04.190 --> 00:02:08.980
I told him not to, but he said he was
so thirsty he couldn't stand it,

30
00:02:08.980 --> 00:02:12.570
so he chomped down
on some cactus growing back there.

31
00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:13.860
Cactus?

32
00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:15.820
Yeah. Over there.

33
00:02:16.200 --> 00:02:17.780
Those round things.

34
00:02:18.530 --> 00:02:20.910
What?! That's bad!

35
00:02:20.910 --> 00:02:24.830
Those are mescal cacti!
They're used in hallucinogens!

36
00:02:24.830 --> 00:02:26.000
What?!

37
00:02:26.920 --> 00:02:28.670
Oh, no!

38
00:02:28.670 --> 00:02:30.420
We're gonna drown!

39
00:02:30.420 --> 00:02:33.550
Alright, you asked for it!

40
00:02:34.050 --> 00:02:36.510
I'll kick all your asses!

41
00:02:38.810 --> 00:02:40.470
This is bad!

42
00:02:40.470 --> 00:02:42.770
Gum-Gum...

43
00:02:45.230 --> 00:02:46.440
Sedative!

44
00:02:46.440 --> 00:02:47.940
Way to go, Chopper!

45
00:02:47.980 --> 00:02:54.950
Yuba, the Town of Rebels

46
00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:53.070
The operation will commence
at high noon two days from now.

47
00:02:53.070 --> 00:02:55.280
Have you made the arrangements?

48
00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:57.530
Yes. All the pieces are in place.

49
00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:02.370
Nanohana has 150 billions
awaiting orders.

50
00:03:02.870 --> 00:03:09.340
Also, I've recalled Mr. 2.
It appears he failed to capture Mr. 3.

51
00:03:10.340 --> 00:03:14.170
At eight o'clock tonight,
all of the officer agents...

52
00:03:15.170 --> 00:03:17.590
will gather at the Spiders Cafe.

53
00:03:18.680 --> 00:03:22.720
The Spiders Cafe,
Baroque Works Headquarters
Kingdom of Alabasta

54
00:03:20.010 --> 00:03:22.720
Yes. Very good.

55
00:03:23.180 --> 00:03:25.730
It's already past five o'clock,

56
00:03:25.730 --> 00:03:29.690
so they're likely
arriving there as we speak.

57
00:03:47.960 --> 00:03:50.460
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!
Merry Christmas! Merry Christmas!

58
00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:53.880
What a long, exhausting trip!
My back's killing me!

59
00:03:53.880 --> 00:03:56.170
Honestly! It's all your fault, Mr. 4!

60
00:03:53.880 --> 00:03:58.380
Miss Merry Christmas
Officer Agent, Baroque Works

61
00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:58.380
My back gave out because of your slow ass!

62
00:03:58.380 --> 00:04:03.350
Mr. 4
Officer Agent, Baroque Works

63
00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:03.850
I... am...

64
00:04:03.850 --> 00:04:05.180
sorry...
Yes! Yes! Yes! Yes!

65
00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:07.600
How's business, Paula?
The shop is empty today!

66
00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:10.860
This shop is empty! Shop’s empty!
Shempty! S-H-E-M-P-T-Y!

67
00:04:11.360 --> 00:04:15.110
It's good to see you again.
Welcome, Miss Merry Christmas,

68
00:04:15.110 --> 00:04:16.320
You as well, Mr. 4.

69
00:04:16.320 --> 00:04:26.080
Paula, Proprietor, Spiders Cafe

70
00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:19.570
You have the place all to yourselves today.

71
00:04:19.570 --> 00:04:22.450
I can make you some orange pekoe and...

72
00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:26.080
Mr. 4, apple tea, was it?

73
00:04:26.080 --> 00:04:29.330
And keep the drink lukewarm!
I can't chug it when it's too hot!

74
00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:33.040
Make some right away!
Right away! Right now! Right away!

75
00:04:33.040 --> 00:04:35.800
You seem lively as ever. How's work?

76
00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:39.050
Failure means death in my world.
Work's never been better!

77
00:04:39.050 --> 00:04:42.050
You bimbo! You bimbo!
You bim-bim-bim!

78
00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:45.640
You're right. I'm sorry.

79
00:04:46.020 --> 00:04:47.930
♪ Un, deux... ♪

80
00:04:46.930 --> 00:04:47.930
♪ ...ourrois! ♪

81
00:04:47.930 --> 00:04:49.480
♪ Un, deux... ♪

82
00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:49.480
♪ ...korrois! ♪

83
00:04:49.850 --> 00:04:55.150
What gives?! The songs at this place
have the strangest lyrics!

84
00:04:55.150 --> 00:04:59.990
Lyrics? No, there's a sonata
playing right now.

85
00:04:59.990 --> 00:05:01.780
There are no words.

86
00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:04.740
♪ Un, deux... ♪

87
00:05:03.410 --> 00:05:04.740
♪ ...ourrois! ♪

88
00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:05.830
Huh?

89
00:05:05.830 --> 00:05:06.700
♪ Un, deux... ♪

90
00:05:06.700 --> 00:05:07.870
♪ ...korrois! ♪

91
00:05:07.870 --> 00:05:09.660
♪ Look down your nose
to your fingertip... ♪

92
00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.710
♪ Un, deux... ♪

93
00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:11.710
♪ ...korrois! ♪

94
00:05:11.710 --> 00:05:13.540
♪ Now kick out your toes! ♪

95
00:05:13.540 --> 00:05:15.340
♪ Un, deux... ♪

96
00:05:14.290 --> 00:05:15.340
♪ ...ourrois! ♪

97
00:05:15.340 --> 00:05:18.630
♪ Like when... you were born... ♪

98
00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:22.470
♪ Lesson! Lesson! ♪

99
00:05:23.850 --> 00:05:26.390
♪ Love and... ♪

100
00:05:26.930 --> 00:05:28.850
♪ mascara! ♪

101
00:05:28.850 --> 00:05:33.350
♪ Nosebleeds with mascara! ♪

102
00:05:33.350 --> 00:05:38.320
– ♪ I'm self made! ♪ 
– ♪ I'm self made! ♪

103
00:05:38.320 --> 00:05:41.200
♪ And... there... fore... ♪

104
00:05:41.700 --> 00:05:43.870
♪ Lesson! ♪

105
00:05:42.700 --> 00:05:43.870
♪ Lesson! ♪

106
00:05:43.870 --> 00:05:46.200
♪ Lesson! ♪

107
00:05:44.870 --> 00:05:46.200
♪ Lesson! ♪

108
00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:49.040
♪ Okama way! ♪

109
00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:51.160
♪ And... smile! ♪

110
00:05:51.160 --> 00:05:52.620
♪ Oh, the greatest! ♪

111
00:05:52.620 --> 00:05:54.040
♪ The greatest! ♪

112
00:05:53.460 --> 00:05:55.460
♪ The greatest! ♪

113
00:05:54.040 --> 00:05:55.460
♪ The greatest! ♪

114
00:05:56.040 --> 00:05:59.760
– ♪ Okama way! ♪ 
– ♪ Okama way! ♪

115
00:06:05.300 --> 00:06:07.470
Greetings!

116
00:06:07.470 --> 00:06:10.520
How do you... deux?

117
00:06:10.520 --> 00:06:11.770
You must be stupid.

118
00:06:11.770 --> 00:06:14.020
I am not stupid, Paula!

119
00:06:14.020 --> 00:06:17.520
But I am a dancer!

120
00:06:17.520 --> 00:06:19.190
One octopar, pretty please!

121
00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:20.110
Octopar?

122
00:06:20.110 --> 00:06:22.070
Nobody's clowning here!

123
00:06:22.070 --> 00:06:24.700
An octopus parfait. Wasn't it obvious?

124
00:06:26.410 --> 00:06:28.870
Oh, you guys can head home now.

125
00:06:28.870 --> 00:06:29.580
– Aye aye, sir!
– Aye aye, sir!

126
00:06:29.910 --> 00:06:33.210
And you'd better not neglect
your dance practice either!

127
00:06:33.210 --> 00:06:34.290
– Aye aye, sir!
– Aye aye, sir!

128
00:06:34.290 --> 00:06:36.250
♪ Un, deux! Un, deux! ♪

129
00:06:36.250 --> 00:06:39.750
Huh? What're fatso
and the old hag doing here?

130
00:06:39.750 --> 00:06:41.050
Zip it, you!

131
00:06:41.050 --> 00:06:44.010
My back gave out
when you started talking!

132
00:06:44.010 --> 00:06:45.930
Oh, right, right, right!

133
00:06:45.930 --> 00:06:51.220
I heard on the grapevine that even
Mr. 1 and his partner will be here.

134
00:06:51.220 --> 00:06:54.770
I've never met them
for whatever reason.

135
00:06:54.770 --> 00:06:56.810
The anticipation is killing me!

136
00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:05.280
I have something for you. Here.

137
00:07:08.450 --> 00:07:11.290
Hold onto it. Always.

138
00:07:11.830 --> 00:07:13.870
Huh? It's just a piece of paper.

139
00:07:13.870 --> 00:07:19.340
It sure is, but that paper will
one day bring us together again.

140
00:07:20.460 --> 00:07:21.840
You don't want it?

141
00:07:22.380 --> 00:07:23.800
No, I want it!

142
00:07:23.800 --> 00:07:26.430
An older brother can't help worrying...

143
00:07:27.930 --> 00:07:30.140
about their kid brother.

144
00:07:30.600 --> 00:07:34.180
I'm sure he's been a handful...

145
00:07:34.180 --> 00:07:35.940
Take care of him for me.

146
00:07:37.310 --> 00:07:39.900
Huh? You're going already?

147
00:07:43.030 --> 00:07:47.700
Luffy! I'll see you at the top
of the pirate world!

148
00:08:09.680 --> 00:08:12.430
Hey. So, Luffy...

149
00:08:11.680 --> 00:08:12.430
Yeah?

150
00:08:12.430 --> 00:08:14.310
What did your brother give you?

151
00:08:14.310 --> 00:08:15.890
Well... I dunno.

152
00:08:16.640 --> 00:08:18.310
It's just a piece of paper.

153
00:08:18.310 --> 00:08:19.690
Just a piece of paper?

154
00:08:19.690 --> 00:08:20.900
Lemme see that.

155
00:08:22.400 --> 00:08:26.860
It really is just a bit of paper.
Not a note, not anything.

156
00:08:29.070 --> 00:08:30.490
What the heck?

157
00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:34.410
I'm not really sure either, but...

158
00:08:38.410 --> 00:08:39.370
Hey! Spit it out!

159
00:08:40.750 --> 00:08:41.750
C'mon...

160
00:08:41.750 --> 00:08:43.380
Luffy, let me see your hat.

161
00:08:43.380 --> 00:08:44.340
Huh? This?

162
00:08:44.340 --> 00:08:48.260
If it's that important, I'll sew it
to the inside of your hat band.

163
00:08:48.260 --> 00:08:50.340
Oh! Great! Sew it in real good!

164
00:08:50.340 --> 00:08:51.720
Well, of course.

165
00:08:53.970 --> 00:08:55.310
Okay! All done!

166
00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:57.270
Here you go!

167
00:08:57.270 --> 00:09:00.230
Thanks! Now I don't have to worry!

168
00:09:00.230 --> 00:09:03.940
There's nothing written on it.
Why would he want you to keep it?

169
00:09:04.570 --> 00:09:08.360
It's enough that Ace told me
to keep it, so I'm keeping it!

170
00:09:08.820 --> 00:09:11.360
I hope your instincts here
are on the money.

171
00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:13.240
It's fine!
They're right lots of times!

172
00:09:13.240 --> 00:09:18.080
I don't know about that...

173
00:09:14.830 --> 00:09:18.080
Someone carry me...

174
00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:23.290
Oh! The night... it grows ever later!

175
00:09:24.210 --> 00:09:26.710
The appointed time
of eight o'clock draws near.

176
00:09:36.390 --> 00:09:38.430
So boring!

177
00:09:40.890 --> 00:09:43.400
I'm so bored I'll just spin around!

178
00:09:44.060 --> 00:09:46.650
Yes, I'll spin. I'll just do that.

179
00:09:46.650 --> 00:09:48.360
Quit it! Now my eyes are spinning!

180
00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:52.150
What of it, you old bitty?!
Want a piece of me?!

181
00:09:52.150 --> 00:09:53.740
I thought you'd never ask!

182
00:09:54.200 --> 00:09:57.700
Come on! Would the two of you
please knock it off?

183
00:10:09.260 --> 00:10:11.920
H-Hey, now!
What happened to you guys?!

184
00:10:11.920 --> 00:10:13.970
Why'd you come
bursting back in here?!

185
00:10:13.970 --> 00:10:15.720
N-No... It was him...

186
00:10:17.180 --> 00:10:20.560
Oh. They're acquaintances of yours?

187
00:10:22.520 --> 00:10:35.490
Mr. 1
Officer Agent, Baroque Works

188
00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:26.610
They were acting suspiciously in the desert.

189
00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:29.570
It's not as if they're dead.

190
00:10:29.570 --> 00:10:33.030
You seem to be on close terms with them,

191
00:10:33.030 --> 00:10:35.490
but such bonds inevitably lead to ruin.

192
00:10:35.490 --> 00:10:37.990
These men are my subordinates!

193
00:10:37.990 --> 00:10:39.870
Stop, Mr. 2!

194
00:10:42.410 --> 00:10:45.210
Un, Deux, Korrois!

195
00:10:46.470 --> 00:10:49.800
Un, Deux, Ourrois!

196
00:10:53.260 --> 00:10:54.880
Bold Change!

197
00:10:54.880 --> 00:10:56.220
Un! Deux!

198
00:11:04.020 --> 00:11:06.020
How in the heck...?!

199
00:11:06.020 --> 00:11:07.560
The wall fell apart for him!

200
00:11:07.560 --> 00:11:09.730
No! He shattered the wall?!

201
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:14.320
I see you have a death wish.

202
00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:18.780
Hold it! That's enough, Mr. 1!

203
00:11:18.780 --> 00:11:23.620
Don't stop me, Miss Doublefinger.
He's a dead man walking.

204
00:11:24.250 --> 00:11:27.290
Stop! Let go of me, fatso!

205
00:11:27.290 --> 00:11:30.210
Mr. 2! You also need to cool it.

206
00:11:30.210 --> 00:11:35.340
It's now eight.
All invited agents are here.

207
00:11:36.090 --> 00:11:40.600
And a letter with orders
has arrived at the Spiders Cafe.

208
00:11:43.220 --> 00:11:47.520
We're to head to Rainbase,
the City of Dreams.

209
00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:52.610
The man we call boss...
whose face we've never seen...

210
00:11:57.700 --> 00:11:59.410
He's there waiting for us.

211
00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:11.420
They should be on their
way here to Rainbase now.

212
00:12:11.460 --> 00:12:16.550
Bunchi
Special All-Terrain Transport Turtle
Baroque Works

213
00:12:14.210 --> 00:12:16.420
I sent Bunchi to get them.

214
00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:18.880
I expect they'll arrive this evening.

215
00:12:23.850 --> 00:12:28.350
You never told us you were
actually Miss Doublefinger...

216
00:12:28.350 --> 00:12:34.230
Miss Doublefinger
Officer Agent, Baroque Works

217
00:12:30.350 --> 00:12:34.230
I don't remember ever saying that I wasn't.

218
00:12:34.900 --> 00:12:39.200
Have you refilled the positions
of the billions we lost in Nanohana?

219
00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:42.450
I've already assigned replacements.

220
00:12:43.080 --> 00:12:48.910
I've dispatched the frilled runners.
They will contact the new billions.

221
00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:51.250
Frilled Runners
Urgent Delivery Force
Baroque Works

222
00:12:55.460 --> 00:12:59.010
I see. Everything is
progressing smoothly.

223
00:13:03.640 --> 00:13:06.390
Up ahead! I see a light!

224
00:13:06.390 --> 00:13:08.520
Did we make it to Yuba?!

225
00:13:08.520 --> 00:13:11.190
I can't really see with all this sand!

226
00:13:12.020 --> 00:13:14.150
That sound... do you hear it?

227
00:13:16.280 --> 00:13:17.900
Something is wrong here!

228
00:13:25.370 --> 00:13:26.740
A sandstorm!

229
00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:33.080
The city of Yuba is caught
in a sandstorm!

230
00:13:46.220 --> 00:13:47.680
Please, no...

231
00:13:47.970 --> 00:13:56.650
Yuba Oasis
Kingdom of Alabasta

232
00:13:50.810 --> 00:13:52.980
This is bad.

233
00:13:52.980 --> 00:13:55.900
It looks the same as that Erumalu city!

234
00:13:57.900 --> 00:13:59.150
Where's the water?!

235
00:13:59.780 --> 00:14:02.610
Wasn't this supposed
to be an oasis, Vivi?

236
00:14:03.110 --> 00:14:05.370
The sand has raised the ground!

237
00:14:06.120 --> 00:14:08.580
The oasis has been swallowed up!

238
00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:16.040
Are you travelers?

239
00:14:16.960 --> 00:14:21.090
You must be exhausted...
from your trek through the desert.

240
00:14:22.590 --> 00:14:27.050
Sorry. This town is a bit dried up.

241
00:14:28.310 --> 00:14:31.430
But feel free to stopover if you need to.

242
00:14:33.560 --> 00:14:41.530
Toto
A Man from Yuba

243
00:14:34.310 --> 00:14:37.020
There are plenty of inns here.

244
00:14:37.020 --> 00:14:40.820
They are this town's pride, after all.

245
00:14:42.190 --> 00:14:46.490
Actually, we came because we heard
the Rebel Army was in this city.

246
00:14:47.070 --> 00:14:49.410
What business do you have
with the Rebel Army?!

247
00:14:49.410 --> 00:14:55.080
You imbeciles! Don't tell me
you're hoping to join the Rebellion?!

248
00:14:59.090 --> 00:15:03.720
If you're looking for those fools,
they left town long ago.

249
00:15:03.720 --> 00:15:06.760
They what?!

250
00:15:06.760 --> 00:15:08.220
No!

251
00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:15.980
A sandstorm hit the town just now,
but rest assured it wasn't the first.

252
00:15:15.980 --> 00:15:20.650
After three years of drought,
all that remains is sand,

253
00:15:20.650 --> 00:15:25.320
and sandstorms have
frequented this town ever since.

254
00:15:25.320 --> 00:15:32.580
Little by little, the oasis is getting
buried, leaving what you see now.

255
00:15:32.580 --> 00:15:36.420
With the town's flow of supplies gone,

256
00:15:36.420 --> 00:15:40.000
the Rebellion's protracted struggle
couldn't last much longer.

257
00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:45.050
So they moved their base to Katorea.

258
00:15:45.800 --> 00:15:47.260
Katorea?!

259
00:15:47.260 --> 00:15:50.930
Where's that, Vivi?!
Is Katorea close by?!

260
00:15:50.930 --> 00:15:53.470
It's an oasis next to Nanohana.

261
00:15:54.100 --> 00:15:57.520
Did we come all this way for nothing?!

262
00:15:58.150 --> 00:15:59.400
Vivi?

263
00:15:59.400 --> 00:16:00.730
Did you just say "Vivi"?

264
00:16:01.190 --> 00:16:05.400
Wait, old guy! Vivi isn't the princess!

265
00:16:03.730 --> 00:16:05.400
Quiet, moron!

266
00:16:07.150 --> 00:16:09.990
Is that Vivi? It is, isn't it?

267
00:16:11.120 --> 00:16:15.160
You're alive! Thank goodness!

268
00:16:15.550 --> 00:16:18.670
It's me! Don't you recognize me?

269
00:16:19.420 --> 00:16:23.420
I suppose I can't blame you.
I did lose some weight...

270
00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:25.760
Uncle... Toto?

271
00:16:28.630 --> 00:16:30.090
That's right!

272
00:16:34.470 --> 00:16:35.890
It can't be...

273
00:16:41.770 --> 00:16:45.280
So long, Vivi-chan.
This is goodbye for now.

274
00:16:45.780 --> 00:16:48.860
When the city is up and running,
come and visit sometime.

275
00:16:48.860 --> 00:16:51.200
I will, Uncle Toto!

276
00:16:53.370 --> 00:16:57.410
Yuba will increase the lushness
of this country.

277
00:17:00.580 --> 00:17:01.670
I know it.

278
00:17:11.390 --> 00:17:13.600
"Toto"? "Uncle"?

279
00:17:13.600 --> 00:17:19.430
Vivi, I have faith in His Majesty!

280
00:17:22.310 --> 00:17:26.610
His character makes him incapable
of betraying his own country.

281
00:17:26.610 --> 00:17:28.320
Don't you agree?!

282
00:17:58.140 --> 00:18:00.850
This uprising is ludicrous!

283
00:18:02.390 --> 00:18:04.900
They're such fools...

284
00:18:05.480 --> 00:18:09.570
Vivi! Grow up to be a great princess!

285
00:18:21.580 --> 00:18:26.250
Kingdom of Alabasta
11 Years Ago

286
00:18:45.060 --> 00:18:48.110
Our village... Our village dried up!

287
00:18:47.150 --> 00:18:50.440
Koza
A Boy from Town

288
00:18:48.110 --> 00:18:50.440
Why didn't you help us?!

289
00:18:51.110 --> 00:18:54.320
But the weather is the will of the gods.

290
00:18:54.320 --> 00:18:59.740
I may be king, but I cannot
control the forces of nature.

291
00:19:00.410 --> 00:19:04.080
But my dad told me
the king can do anything!

292
00:19:04.460 --> 00:19:08.460
I can only do what
can be done by man–

293
00:19:08.460 --> 00:19:11.550
Your Majesty! The boy's father
just arrived at the palace.

294
00:19:11.550 --> 00:19:14.340
My deepest apologies, Your Majesty!

295
00:19:14.340 --> 00:19:16.340
Forgive my precocious son!

296
00:19:14.380 --> 00:19:18.350
Toto, the Boy's Father
(The Man from Yuba)

297
00:19:16.340 --> 00:19:18.350
I take full responsibility!

298
00:19:18.970 --> 00:19:23.310
Punish me, not him! I will
do better! Please, I beg of you!

299
00:19:23.310 --> 00:19:26.770
I can't believe how foolish
you are... Such a fool...!

300
00:19:26.770 --> 00:19:31.230
Such a fool! Such a fool!
Such a fool! Such a fool!

301
00:19:31.230 --> 00:19:34.440
Your name is Toto, is it not?

302
00:19:34.440 --> 00:19:35.490
Sire!

303
00:19:35.950 --> 00:19:41.450
The kingdom will send relief
to villagers affected by the drought.

304
00:19:41.450 --> 00:19:46.920
I grant you residence in Alubarna,
so you may plan for your future!

305
00:19:46.920 --> 00:19:52.590
Oh, how gracious is His Majesty!
Thank you! Thank you!

306
00:19:53.630 --> 00:19:57.300
Just stuff it! You just don't get
how the villagers feel!

307
00:19:57.970 --> 00:20:00.300
Wait! Koza! Get back here!

308
00:20:02.560 --> 00:20:03.560
Toto.

309
00:20:03.560 --> 00:20:04.680
Sire!

310
00:20:05.930 --> 00:20:10.650
What a fine lad. He provided
insight to the villagers' hearts.

311
00:20:10.650 --> 00:20:16.610
He stormed in here
for the sake of his community.

312
00:20:20.620 --> 00:20:22.030
What a crybaby.

313
00:20:25.540 --> 00:20:27.250
You talking to me, shorty?

314
00:20:28.460 --> 00:20:29.580
Your Majesty.

315
00:20:30.080 --> 00:20:31.380
What is it, Igaram?

316
00:20:31.380 --> 00:20:32.540
With all due respect,

317
00:20:33.040 --> 00:20:37.470
the country cannot afford
the relief that they need.

318
00:20:37.470 --> 00:20:38.880
Use your head!

319
00:20:38.880 --> 00:20:43.100
Then we cut back on our own
expenses or any such excess!

320
00:20:43.100 --> 00:20:45.850
Understood. As you wish.

321
00:20:46.640 --> 00:20:49.770
It's terrible, Your Majesty!
It's Princess Vivi!

322
00:20:52.980 --> 00:20:55.280
I had a fight. I lost.

323
00:20:55.280 --> 00:20:57.610
Vivi!

324
00:20:56.280 --> 00:20:57.610
Princess Vivi!

325
00:20:57.610 --> 00:21:00.950
That little punk!
How dare he harm a princess!

326
00:21:00.950 --> 00:21:04.580
I'll pulverize him! I swear he's dead meat!

327
00:21:02.700 --> 00:21:04.580
Wait! Wait! Igaram!

328
00:21:04.580 --> 00:21:07.540
My deepest apologies!

329
00:21:07.540 --> 00:21:10.250
Take my life as restitution!

330
00:21:10.250 --> 00:21:13.880
Enough, both of you!

331
00:21:16.670 --> 00:21:20.630
Do not be rash!
It was a mere children's quarrel!

332
00:21:20.680 --> 00:21:27.810
Capital City, Alubarna

333
00:21:27.850 --> 00:21:29.980
City Outskirts

334
00:21:28.770 --> 00:21:29.980
It's a showdown!

335
00:21:29.980 --> 00:21:32.850
Come on over!
Fight! Fight!

336
00:21:33.980 --> 00:21:35.980
Let that princess have it!

337
00:21:35.980 --> 00:21:38.740
Put that smart-ass royal
in her place!

338
00:21:38.740 --> 00:21:41.110
You can do it, Vivi!

339
00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:44.620
Hey, you! Koza's
our leader, you know!

340
00:21:48.330 --> 00:21:52.250
If I win, I get to be your leader!

341
00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:55.340
Like I'd ever lose to you, short stuff!

342
00:21:55.790 --> 00:21:58.550
In my village,
I've always been the leader.

343
00:22:00.380 --> 00:22:01.880
Here goes!

344
00:22:17.860 --> 00:22:19.320
Listen, everyone!

345
00:22:19.730 --> 00:22:23.610
As of today, Vivi is the vice leader
of our Sand-Sand Clan!

346
00:22:23.610 --> 00:22:25.320
Anyone got a problem with that?!

347
00:22:25.320 --> 00:22:27.830
– No!
– No!

348
00:22:29.040 --> 00:22:30.660
Look, Igaram.

349
00:22:31.290 --> 00:22:33.670
Vivi has made friends.

350
00:22:34.290 --> 00:22:35.250
Yes.

351
00:22:35.250 --> 00:22:39.880
If she is to carry Alabasta
on her shoulders someday,

352
00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:42.130
friendship will be of vital importance.

353
00:22:48.680 --> 00:22:49.850
Aha!

354
00:22:50.810 --> 00:22:53.560
Uncle and Mrs. Toto! Good morning!

355
00:22:53.560 --> 00:22:54.640
Where's Leader?

356
00:22:54.640 --> 00:22:58.650
Oh, good morning! If you're looking
for Koza, he already took off!

357
00:22:59.110 --> 00:23:00.980
I assume he's at the usual spot.

358
00:23:00.980 --> 00:23:02.440
Thank you kindly!

359
00:23:02.820 --> 00:23:05.910
Oh, Vivi! Will you stay for lunch?

360
00:23:05.910 --> 00:23:08.120
I would love to! Thanks!

361
00:23:09.240 --> 00:23:11.750
This country is certainly an odd one.

362
00:23:11.750 --> 00:23:16.080
The princess of a kingdom,
mingling with commoners like us!

363
00:23:16.080 --> 00:23:18.080
It's proof of peace!

364
00:23:19.250 --> 00:23:21.550
Sir Igaram, will you
also join us for lunch?

365
00:23:21.550 --> 00:23:24.220
No, no, that's quite all right!
I brought rice balls!

366
00:23:24.220 --> 00:23:25.430
Pardon me!

367
00:23:34.310 --> 00:23:36.980
Your Majesty!
What are you doing here?!

368
00:23:38.440 --> 00:23:39.690
Sire!

369
00:23:41.150 --> 00:23:43.490
You're following me again?!

370
00:23:43.490 --> 00:23:48.450
B-But I just cannot help
but worry about my little Vivi!

371
00:23:49.990 --> 00:23:53.330
Return home! You're creating
extra work for me!

372
00:23:53.330 --> 00:23:54.960
What?!

373
00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:57.790
Don't give me, "What?!"

374
00:24:11.260 --> 00:24:13.430
Heya, girlie!

375
00:24:13.430 --> 00:24:16.560
Goin' somewhere?
We'll take you there.

376
00:24:19.350 --> 00:24:21.610
Attack, Sand-Sand Clan!

377
00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:27.110
You've gotta be jokin'!
These kids won't go down!

378
00:24:27.820 --> 00:24:28.990
Leader! Everyone!

379
00:24:28.990 --> 00:24:32.660
Run, Vivi! These guys
are out to get you!

380
00:24:32.660 --> 00:24:34.740
Get going, Vivi!

381
00:24:34.740 --> 00:24:36.040
They're gonna kill you!

382
00:24:36.040 --> 00:24:37.910
But... Leader!

383
00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:42.210
We ain't gonna kill ya!

384
00:24:42.210 --> 00:24:46.170
We just wanna hold her for ransom,
so this here's a kidnappin'!

385
00:24:47.880 --> 00:24:48.840
Damn you!

386
00:24:49.840 --> 00:24:52.680
Just come with us, Princess Vivi!

387
00:24:57.980 --> 00:24:59.390
Like hell she will!

388
00:24:59.390 --> 00:25:01.940
Protect her to the death,
Sand-Sand Clan!

389
00:25:01.940 --> 00:25:03.110
– Yeah!
– Yeah!
